The paper deals with compressed sensing and distributed compressed sensing, which are topics covered in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Signal Processing (cs.SP) sub-categories. The focus on jointly sparse signal ensembles and multimeasurement vector (MMV) problems suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the use of belief propagation and the identification of a phase transition suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
